类 MultiVariantExpression

  • 所有已实现的接口:
    java.lang.Cloneable, ExpressionItem
    public class MultiVariantExpression
extends Operator
    Suffix expression constructed from an infix expression. To contruct an MultiVariantExpression you need an infix expression String and a dictionary of Operator. To simplize the construction of operator map, we provide xyz.davidchangx.mathtool.OperatorMapGenerator to generate operator map conveniently. You can use the operators provided in package xyz.davidchangx.algorithms.math.operator, and also you can contribute your own operators by inherit class Operator. This class inherits Operator class so that a contributed MultiVariantExpression can be used as a new operator in another MultiVariantExpression or Expression.
    从以下版本开始:
    3.0
    版本:
    4.0
    作者:
    David Chang

      • MultiVariantExpression

        public MultiVariantExpression​(java.lang.String functionName,
                              int inStackPriority,
                              int outStackPriority,
                              java.lang.String infix,
                              java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,Operator> operatorMap,
                              java.lang.String... x)
                       throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                              java.io.IOException
        Constructs an MultiVariantExpression object from given function name, in-stack and out-stack priority, infix string, an operator map and the character of unknown. The returned object can be used as a new Operator, string format of which is functionName, group mode of which is OperatorGroupMode.NEEDING_CLOSED, operand count of which is the count of the unknowns.
        参数:
        functionName - a given function name that can be used as a new operator's string format
        inStackPriority - in-stack priority. We advise to set this priority as 15.
        outStackPriority - out-stack priority. We advise to set this priority as 1.
        infix - the infix expression string
        operatorMap - the operator map
        x - the character of unknown
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the infix cannot be correctly scanned.
        java.io.IOException
